   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 4 — Load raw data + drop PII/high-cardinality fields\n",
    "\n",
    "Raw data is loaded once at the opportunity level to preserve a canonical transaction log.  \n",
    "PII and high-cardinality text fields are removed to keep the public repo safe and to reduce non-generalizable leakage-like identifiers."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "99b3f00a-8e16-4a9f-85d2-537f99079d20",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Raw shape: (221124, 28)\n",
      "Dropped PII cols: ['account_name', 'opportunity_name', 'primary_campaign_source', 'primary_contact', 'billing_city', 'billing_zip_postal_code']\n",
      "Post-drop shape: (221124, 22)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Raw data is loaded once at the opportunity level to preserve a single canonical source of truth.\n",
    "df_raw = pd.read_csv(RAW_PATH, encoding=\"cp1252\")\n",
    "print(\"Raw shape:\", df_raw.shape)\n",
    "\n",
    "# PII/high-cardinality columns are removed to keep the public repo safe and to avoid sparse, non-generalizable features.\n",
    "PII_COLS = [\n",
    "    \"account_name\",\n",
    "    \"opportunity_name\",\n",
    "    \"primary_campaign_source\",\n",
    "    \"primary_contact\",\n",
    "    \"billing_city\",\n",
    "    \"billing_zip_postal_code\",\n",
    "]\n",
    "PII_COLS = [c for c in PII_COLS if c in df_raw.columns]\n",
    "df = df_raw.drop(columns=PII_COLS).copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Dropped PII cols:\", PII_COLS)\n",
    "print(\"Post-drop shape:\", df.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1e77ce83-0ed4-4386-bf65-d694693ac877",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 5 — Type normalization + de-duplication + audit checks\n",
    "\n",
    "Dates and numeric types are enforced to make year extraction and aggregations reliable.  \n",
    "Text normalization is applied to avoid encoding artifacts.  \n",
    "Duplicates are removed using a stable transaction identifier (`opportunity_id`), and audit prints validate assumptions during review."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "0dea2974-7e36-41cc-adf5-4ec3211803e9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "/tmp/ipykernel_1242/499077905.py:9: UserWarning: Could not infer format, so each element will be parsed individually, falling back to `dateutil`. To ensure parsing is consistent and as-expected, please specify a format.\n",
      "  df[\"close_date\"] = pd.to_datetime(df[\"close_date\"], errors=\"coerce\")\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Clean shape: (221086, 23)\n",
      "Duplicate opportunity_id: 0\n",
      "Date range: 2013-01-01 00:00:00 -> 2026-08-20 00:00:00\n",
      "Non-positive amounts: 11162\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Text normalization is applied to reduce encoding artifacts and keep downstream grouping stable.\n",
    "def _to_ascii(x):\n",
    "    if pd.isna(x):\n",
    "        return x\n",
    "    s = str(x)\n",
    "    return unicodedata.normalize(\"NFKD\", s).encode(\"ascii\", \"ignore\").decode(\"ascii\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Date and numeric types are enforced to make year extraction and aggregations reliable.\n",
    "df[\"close_date\"] = pd.to_datetime(df[\"close_date\"], errors=\"coerce\")\n",
    "df[\"amount\"] = pd.to_numeric(df[\"amount\"], errors=\"coerce\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Key identifiers are required for linking donors/transactions and for defining the donor-year panel.\n",
    "df = df.dropna(subset=[\"account_id\", \"opportunity_id\", \"close_date\", \"amount\"]).copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Donation year is extracted explicitly to support donor×year aggregation and temporal splitting.\n",
    "df[\"donation_year\"] = df[\"close_date\"].dt.year.astype(int)\n",
    "\n",
    "# String columns are cleaned for consistent joins/groupbys across platforms and exports.\n",
    "for col in df.select_dtypes(include=[\"object\", \"string\"]).columns:\n",
    "    df[col] = df[col].astype(\"string\").str.strip()\n",
    "    df[col] = df[col].map(_to_ascii)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Duplicates are removed twice: first full-row, then by stable transaction id.\n",
    "df = df.drop_duplicates()\n",
    "df = df.drop_duplicates(subset=[\"opportunity_id\"], keep=\"first\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# A small audit printout is kept to validate assumptions during live review.\n",
    "print(\"Clean shape:\", df.shape)\n",
    "print(\"Duplicate opportunity_id:\", int(df[\"opportunity_id\"].duplicated().sum()))\n",
    "print(\"Date range:\", df[\"close_date\"].min(), \"->\", df[\"close_date\"].max())\n",
    "print(\"Non-positive amounts:\", int((df[\"amount\"] <= 0).sum()))"
   ]
  },
