   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 17 — Shared metric utilities (PR curve + summary)\n",
    "\n",
    "Shared evaluation utilities keep comparisons consistent across models and make the walkthrough easier to follow.  \n",
    "AUPRC is emphasized because class imbalance makes accuracy misleading for lapse prediction."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "id": "799cdd27-ec47-4949-be1d-9c282da2c0d2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Shared evaluation utilities keep metrics consistent across models and make the live walkthrough smoother.\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import (\n",
    "    average_precision_score,\n",
    "    precision_recall_curve,\n",
    "    precision_recall_fscore_support,\n",
    "    brier_score_loss,\n",
    ")\n",
    "from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\n",
    "from sklearn.calibration import CalibratedClassifierCV, calibration_curve\n",
    "\n",
    "from xgboost import XGBClassifier\n",
    "\n",
    "def eval_probs(y_true, y_prob, threshold=0.5):\n",
    "    y_pred = (y_prob >= threshold).astype(int)\n",
    "    p, r, f1, _ = precision_recall_fscore_support(y_true, y_pred, average=\"binary\", zero_division=0)\n",
    "    auprc = average_precision_score(y_true, y_prob)\n",
    "    return {\"precision\": float(p), \"recall\": float(r), \"f1\": float(f1), \"AUPRC\": float(auprc)}\n",
    "\n",
    "def plot_pr_curve(y_true, y_prob, title):\n",
    "    prec, rec, _ = precision_recall_curve(y_true, y_prob)\n",
    "    plt.figure()\n",
    "    plt.plot(rec, prec)\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(\"Recall\")\n",
    "    plt.ylabel(\"Precision\")\n",
    "    plt.title(title)\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3275a748-a4b4-4b40-abe7-b909c2cdcbbb",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 18 — Logistic Regression baseline (tune on VAL, refit on train+val)\n",
    "\n",
    "Logistic Regression provides a strong, interpretable baseline with scaling and class balancing.  \n",
    "Hyperparameters are tuned on validation and then the final baseline is refit on train+val before testing."
