    "## Cell 20 — XGBoost (tune on VAL with early stopping, refit)\n",
    "\n",
    "XGBoost is the primary model because it captures nonlinearities and feature interactions suggested by EDA.  \n",
    "Early stopping on validation improves generalization and reduces unnecessary training rounds."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 22,
   "id": "b46e874c-3d50-45a7-8b1e-2af6b119ea30",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Best XGB: {'params': {'max_depth': 3, 'learning_rate': 0.1}, 'best_iter': 197, 'val_auprc': 0.7943548288146292}\n",
      "XGB TEST metrics: {'precision': 0.7321428571428571, 'recall': 0.6991634491634492, 'f1': 0.7152732060566162, 'AUPRC': 0.7542816294226877}\n"
     ]
