   "source": [
    "# SECTION E — Calibration + Decision-Oriented Top-K Policy\n",
    "\n",
    "This section aligns evaluation with how the model is actually used: ranking donors for limited outreach capacity.  \n",
    "Calibration is applied so predicted scores behave like interpretable probabilities for policy decisions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e46b1e93-f8d9-4c3a-808e-2dcfbabb8d08",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 21 — Calibrate XGBoost + calibration curve\n",
    "\n",
    "Probability calibration (sigmoid/Platt scaling) is applied so predicted probabilities reflect meaningful risk estimates.  \n",
    "Brier score and a calibration curve quantify whether probability outputs are well-behaved."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "id": "590821b6-35e7-4189-a54b-e892522a4a04",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Uncalibrated XGB: {'precision': 0.7321428571428571, 'recall': 0.6991634491634492, 'f1': 0.7152732060566162, 'AUPRC': 0.7542816294226877} | Brier: 0.22367489337921143\n",
      "Calibrated XGB: {'precision': 0.6801685787871693, 'recall': 0.9346846846846847, 'f1': 0.7873695622713105, 'AUPRC': 0.7542816294226877} | Brier: 0.2109764669036884\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Calibration is applied so predicted scores can be interpreted as meaningful risk estimates for outreach decisions.\n",
    "from sklearn.calibration import CalibratedClassifierCV, calibration_curve\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import brier_score_loss\n",
    "from sklearn.frozen import FrozenEstimator\n",
    "\n",
    "# The already-trained XGBoost model is wrapped so calibration treats it as fixed (prefit behavior, sklearn-compatible).\n",
    "cal = CalibratedClassifierCV(\n",
    "    estimator=FrozenEstimator(xgb_final),\n",
    "    method=\"sigmoid\",\n",
    "    cv=5\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calibration is fit on the validation year only to avoid leaking test-year outcomes into probability scaling.\n",
    "cal.fit(X_val, y_val)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calibrated probabilities are produced for the final holdout test year.\n",
    "cal_prob = cal.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Brier score is used to quantify probability quality (lower is better).\n",
    "base_brier = float(brier_score_loss(y_test, xgb_test_prob))\n",
    "cal_brier  = float(brier_score_loss(y_test, cal_prob))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Uncalibrated XGB:\", eval_probs(y_test, xgb_test_prob), \"| Brier:\", base_brier)\n",
    "print(\"Calibrated XGB:\",   eval_probs(y_test, cal_prob),      \"| Brier:\", cal_brier)\n",
    "\n",
    "# A calibration curve is plotted to visualize reliability of predicted probabilities.\n",
    "prob_true, prob_pred = calibration_curve(y_test, cal_prob, n_bins=10)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure()\n",
    "plt.plot(prob_pred, prob_true, marker=\"o\")\n",
    "plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], \"--\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Predicted probability\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Observed frequency\")\n",
    "plt.title(f\"Calibration Curve — XGBoost (Test {TEST_YEAR})\")\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
